[<p>Forty-five percent of Nevada voters who were surveyed said they support Clinton while\xa044 percent back\xa0Trump. Libertarian candidate Gary Johnson received five percent in the poll.</p>, <p>The <a href="/web/20161004060539/http://m.reviewjournal.com/politics/election-2016/rj-s-nevada-poll-shows-clinton-and-trump-are-statistical-tie">survey</a>, conducted by Bendixen &amp; Amandi International and commissioned by the Las Vegas Review-Journal, questioned\xa0800 voters from Sept. 27 to Sept. 29 and has a plus or minus 3.5 percent margin of error.</p>, <p>Because Clinton is leading Trump by one point within the margin of error, the two candidates are statistically tied.</p>, <p>The <a href="/web/20161004060539/http://www.realclearpolitics.com/epolls/2016/president/nv/nevada_trump_vs_clinton_vs_johnson-6004.html"><em>Real Clear Politics</em></a> polling average reveals Trump leading Clinton by less than one point in Nevada, 0.2 percent.</p>]